<p>
	<h3>Growing</h3>
</p>

<p>
	<strong>Can seeds be planted straight into normal soil?</strong> You will greatly improve your vegetables by keeping your soil in good condition. This means thoroughly digging and turning your soil prior to sowing, and ideally adding plenty of organic matter such as soil improver or compost.
</p>

<p>
	<strong>How should I store my excess seeds that haven't been sown?</strong> If you find yourself with too many seeds, most can be kept for sowing the following weeks. By staggering your sowing you can stagger (and extend) the cropping period. Make sure you store spare seeds somewhere cool, dark and dry to keep them dormant.
</p>

<p>
	<h3>Requirements</h3>
</p>

<p>
	<strong>How much space will I need?</strong> Our growing programme is perfect for small family gardens. If you don't have enough space to plant all the seeds each month, you can stagger your sowing to extend the cropping period. We will soon be adding smaller 'window-box' and larger 'allotment' options. 
</p>

<p>	
	<strong>Do I need a greenhouse or cold-frame?</strong> If you're lucky enough to have either, then great, but we understand that not everyone does. That's why we have designed as many of our seeds as possible to be sown straight into the ground. There may be occasions when you will need to sow indoors, but a warm window will suffice - and we will always advise you when this is the case.
</p>

<p>
  <strong>What do I need?</strong> We're not expecting you to go out and buy lots of equipment - we're keeping things simple here. But the following would come in handy:
    <ul>
      <li>You will need something to plant your seeds in, which means some seed trays and potting compost from your local garden centre.</li>
      <li>To keep your seeds happy and make them grow big and strong, some of them will be better off being protected, so a propagator (a plastic cover or cling film) and a sunny window sill will give them a good head start.</li>
      <li>Space to plant. Just a patch of soil is all you need here, but stick a fork in it a few times will help improve your soil condition.</li>
    </ul>
</p>

<p>
	<strong>How many people will I be able to feed?</strong> The vegetable growing programme is intended to supplement the diet of a couple, or a small family, depending on the amount of growing space that is set aside. We are not suggesting that SeedPod alone will be able to feed a family.	
</p>

<p>
	<h3>Environment</h3>
</p>

<p>
	<strong>How much of the packaging can be recycled?</strong> All of our packaging is 100% recyclable, even the outer envelope is padded with shredded paper and can be popped into your paper recycling bin. Better yet, tear it up and add it to your compost.
</p>

<p>
	<strong>What are food miles?</strong>This is the distance that items of food have travelled in order to reach your plate from wherever it was produced. Home growing your own food means you can reduce the amount of energy used to transport food around the globe, thereby reducing the harmful impact upon the environment.


